text.tspan: Chip is square, shown as a breakout.
The notation SDA.3 means Wire.swap(3). You must choose SDA.3 and SCL.3 or SDA.2 and SCL.2 together. Each peripheral can have only one swap position set. Signals are often suffixed by the

peripheral number so RX1 is UART1 rx. In a few cases n,FN is used (2,OUT.1). The notation SDAs.3/SCLs.3 is where the slave pins are in dual mode. Data from AVR64DD32 dfp.2.1.152. Diagrams by ObviousInRetrospect.
